Sorry we don't have more solid repro steps for this one, but to add some more context, what our code is doing here is recursively looping through the elements in a jsp looking for a particular taglib definition. It starts at the Document itself, and since this is two layers into the stack it looks like it is on the first child of the Document.

The NPE happened while calling item(index i) on a NodeList retrieved by calling getChildNodes().

Here's a code snippet:

        // "node" here is most likely the first child of the Document
        NodeList children = node.getChildNodes();
        for( int i=0; i<children.getLength(); i++ )
        {
            Node child = children.item(i); // this is the call that npe'd
            if ( child instanceof Element )
            {
                String candidate = findTaglibFromNS( jspFile, child, taglibURN, webProject );
                if ( candidate != null )
                    return candidate;
            }
        }

